<subSubSection id="C35D656A7A72FF8CFF1CF97CEDE4FE7E" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A72FF8CFF1CF97CEDE4FE7E" blockId="13.[151,1437,1445,2010]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A72FF8EFF1CF97CED7DF8D1" bold="true" box="[199,308,1769,1794]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is atypical with its short, compressed preatrial aedeagal paraphysis and blunt apex, short, membranous shaft, lateral basal teeth and elongate apophysis of the style. All other species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A72FF8EFACAF898E9D5F8F5" authority="Stiller, 2019" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[1297,1436,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A72FF8EFACAF898E9D5F8F5" box="[1297,1436,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Discolopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the aedeagal paraphysis elongated and rounded, the aedeagus lacking basal teeth and a short membranous shaft and the style apophysis shorter. Macrosetae of the subgenital plate are variable in length and distribution. Of the seven dissected males, one subgenital plate of one specimen had the macrosetae in the distal half, another specimen had macrosetae in both plates in the distal half, and five specimens had macrosetae in the distal 2/3 of the plate. In most specimens the macrosetae of one plate were longer than the macrosetae of the other plate. The subgenital plates in intact specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFDBAFF0CEEBEFF63" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[609,759,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFDBAFF0CEEBEFF63" box="[609,759,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFCEAFF0CEFF0FF63" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[817,953,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colopeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFCEAFF0CEFF0FF63" box="[817,953,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. colopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be distinguished. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFA5AFF0CED75FF07" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antizomavorus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFA5AFF0CED75FF07" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. antizomavorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFE91FF28EDF8FF07" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[330,433,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFE91FF28EDF8FF07" box="[330,433,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFE3DFF28EE33FF06" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[486,634,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFE3DFF28EE33FF06" box="[486,634,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected at Biesiesfontein, but only those on 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFB60FF29E9D5FF07" box="[1211,1436,188,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Antizoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="miersiana">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFB60FF29E9D5FF07" box="[1211,1436,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Antizoma miersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included in the former. 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFE01FF4AEEFCFF2B" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[474,693,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arctus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFE01FF4AEEFCFF2B" box="[474,693,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Discolopeus arctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the short crown, and male and female genitalia. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFE72FE90EE78FECE" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[425,561,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colopeus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFE72FE90EE78FECE" box="[425,561,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. colopeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C474D627A70FF8CFDB1FE90EF49FECE" authorityName="Stiller" authorityYear="2019" box="[618,768,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Discolopeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diacaenus">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A70FF8CFDB1FE90EF49FECE" box="[618,768,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">D. diacaenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
