<figureCitation id="137C2A647A70FF8CFCC6FEFAEF20FE5B" box="[797,873,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1761,1783]" captionTargetBox="[160,1436,215,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[160,1445,215,1727]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1a–n. Discolopeus diacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawings. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus with tooth subapically and apically respectively, laterally; f, g. Aedeagus with tooth subapically and apically respectively, dorsally; h, i. Style, dorsally, specimen with subapical teeth on aedeagal shaft and apically on shaft respectively; j. Connective, posterior view; k. Connective, dorsally; l Apex, aedeagal process, laterally; m. Style and aedeagus, laterally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626813/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
